Key Match Events: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 33 points on 11-for-23 shooting.
Oklahoma City Thunder held Boston Celtics to 19.6% shooting from deep.
Boston Celtics made just nine of their 46 three-point attempts.
OKC defense held the Celtics to a season-low 27 points in the first half.
Thunder forced 16 turnovers and held Boston to 92 points.
Oklahoma City had 11 steals and 13 fast break points.
